
[1]crest

   CREST, n. [L. This is probably, a growing or shooting up, from the root
   of cresco.]

   1. The plume of feathers or other material on the top of the ancient
   helmet; the helmet itself.

   2. The ornament of the helmet in heraldry.

   3. The comb of a cock; also, a tuft of feathers on the head of other
   fowls.

   4. Any tuft or ornament worn on the head.

   5. Loftiness; pride; courage; spirit; a lofty mien.

                                 CREST, v.t.

   1. To furnish with a crest; to serve as a crest for.

   2. To mark with long streaks.
